Revolutionary work of the Church Music
At the end of the celebrations on the occasion of its 160-year anniversary of the Liederkranz Dunningen two services with the "Deutsche Messe" by Franz Schubert will frame it.
After the great success of the musical "Rock My Life", the enthusiastic spectators in the spring of this year, the Liederkranz is the closing of the Jubilee enrich two services with the performance of Deutsche Messe by Franz Schubert.
On Saturday 26 October, this extraordinary exhibition is from 19 during the evening Mass in St. Martinus Church Dunningen and on Sunday, 27 October can be heard from 10.15 clock in the service at St. John Baptist Church in Lackendorf.
The so-called German Mass with the original title "songs to celebrate the holy sacrifice of the Mass", D 872, is a spiritual music work of the composer Franz Schubert from 1826 and was at the time when almost revolutionary.
